bug.short_desc: Redraw, Focus and Scrolling bug in qx.ui.table.Table

long_desc.thetext:
A qx.ui.table.Table which has no metacolumns does not handle clicks and focus drawing correctly when clicks occur in the first 10 to 20 lines.
I've attached a testcase which is runable from framework/applications/sample/source/html/test which demonstrates the misbehaviour.
Please click fast on different lines and cells within the first 10 lines.
Attached is also a screen snapshot showing the effect of the bug.
This is for Internet Explorer 7 in Windows XPSP2.
Firefox 2 and Internet Explorer 6 are not affected.

Created attachment 117 Testcase showing the bug
Testcase should be run from frontend/application/sample/source/html/test
Created attachment 118 screen snapshot showing the bug

Please note that the bug only shows up if no metacolumns are used and the table has lots of rows.
The tests Table_1.html to Table_4.html all have two metacolumns defined.
Table_5.html has to few rows to trigger the bug.
This may be the same problem as in bug #314.

A workaround is to create a qx.ui.table.Table with two metacolumns:
table.setMetaColumnCounts([1, -1]);
Tested this with 0.7 trunk rev. 6739. Set version to 0.7. Maybe this gets more attention.

Seems to be a layout issue in IE.
There is no known workaround available. Til and I have investigated some hours, but it really seems to be some crazy IE phenomen.
Maybe we can take a look again at this at a later time.
I am happy for all new workarounds which will be available from the community. And feedback or ideas are really appreaciated.

I tried to reproduce the behaviour without success with rev. 8813 of trunk.
@Sebastian and Til: Are you able to reproduce this with current trunk?
OK, I was able to reproduce this again. So it is present. Weird behaviour!

Reopened as resolved later.
This shouldn't get lost.
